## Objective
- Remove all but 1 message from the messages page (keep one static or first).
- Add the (other) messages as config in /configs/messages.toml (probably [[message]] with sender, relation, text, color, gradient).
- Update config parser (config.ts) and types to include messages.
- Make them openable: in MessageList or page, clicking a message opens it (e.g. full screen overlay, or expand in place with Pretext or larger view, haptic, close button). Keep the grid or list for closed view.

## Constraints / Invariants
- Update parser to handle messages.toml similar to gifts/scenes (parse to array).
- One message remains in page (hardcoded or from config), others loaded.
- Openable: nice interaction, preserves PretextShift for text, aero styles.
- IIPS, no breakage to other tomls.
- Config must drive the data.

## Verification
- messages.toml exists with data.
- Page shows 1 + loads others.
- Click opens (e.g. modal or detail view).
- Build, no parser errors.
- Grep for removed hardcoded.
